      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The myth that universal healthcare stifles innovation and leads to wait times is a myth perpetuated by the pharmaceutical and healthcare industries, which have a vested interest in maintaining the status quo. In reality, countries with universal healthcare systems have actually seen increased innovation and investment in healthcare research, as the focus shifts from profit to people. The US, with its fragmented system, is actually a prime example of how the private sector can lead to inefficiencies and unequal access to care.",
