      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, you're saying the arguments for the private sector are just manufactured by corporations. but what about the actual economic principle of competition? if the government controls everything, don't we lose the incentive to improve services? it feels like you're dismissing anyone who disagrees as just being 'bought' rather than looking at the actual policy drawbacks.",
